    "description": "A political satire micro-management arcade game.<br />\r\nBalance your time juggling a series of responsiblities in the ever chaotic City of Detroit, and see how long you can last!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCompete for highscores in each of three gamemodes<br />\r\nChoose to become a Woke revolutionary, a Cringe fencesitter, or a Based patriot, and venture boldly out into the world of Detriot<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSetup roadblocks to manage civil unrest on the city streets<br />\r\nShare, Like, and Ban social media posts<br />\r\nVote like a contrarian or use your ballot to support diversity<br />\r\nWave the flag like a true patriot<br />\r\nRelocate polling stations to favourable districts<br />\r\nProtect the border from smugglers<br />\r\nTend the grill<br />\r\nBring both sides back to the negotiating table<br />\r\nStuff the ballot<br />\r\nProtect the markets from inflation<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlayable with either mouse (point and click), keyboard (wasd/arrow keys and space/enter), or controller (left joystick and action buttons)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nProgrammed by Cameron James Low<br />\r\nMusic by Daniel Brennan",
